in comparison
to what's in this folder.

521
00:43:13,483 --> 00:43:15,515
Here, take a look.

522
00:43:17,415 --> 00:43:18,948
There's nothing
you don't already know,

523
00:43:19,048 --> 00:43:23,314
but it's good to refresh
your memory sometimes.

524
00:43:23,981 --> 00:43:26,280
This conversation is off
to a strange start.

525
00:43:26,447 --> 00:43:27,713
How so?

526
00:43:27,846 --> 00:43:30,679
I thought we were going to talk
about your friend.

527
00:43:30,779 --> 00:43:33,645
As in, about our litigation
or something else?

528
00:43:33,745 --> 00:43:34,878
Something else.

529
00:43:35,011 --> 00:43:37,144
You must mean his unlawful detention?

530
00:43:37,244 --> 00:43:40,844
Article 301
of the Russian Criminal Code.

531
00:43:42,143 --> 00:43:43,977
It's good you've been notified.

532
00:43:44,576 --> 00:43:48,476
Vadim, it would be great
if you saw to it that justice is served

533
00:43:48,608 --> 00:43:50,775
and those responsible
for this outrage are punished.

534
00:43:50,875 --> 00:43:52,275
I would be glad to help, but...

535
00:43:52,407 --> 00:43:56,507
But you don't see what's in it for you?
Just look in the folder.

536
00:43:56,640 --> 00:43:57,940
Take a look.

537
00:43:58,440 --> 00:44:02,173
You'll see that Kolya's release
is only the first step.

538
00:44:02,305 --> 00:44:03,905
Here's what I think we'll do,

539
00:44:05,238 --> 00:44:07,971
young man.

540
00:44:10,704 --> 00:44:14,903
I'll let your Kolya out,
and you'll gather your stuff

541
00:44:16,170 --> 00:44:18,169
and quietly go back

542
00:44:18,269 --> 00:44:20,401
to where you came from.

543
00:44:20,501 --> 00:44:23,201
- To Moscow?
- Yeah, back to Moscow.

544
00:44:23,334 --> 00:44:26,900
Vadim, I'm afraid
Ivan would not have that.

545
00:44:29,399 --> 00:44:31,699
He'd say,
"Dima, why didn't you do

546
00:44:31,833 --> 00:44:34,632
"everything in your power
to restore justice?"

547
00:44:38,198 --> 00:44:41,464
You know Ivan personally?

548
00:44:41,597 --> 00:44:42,597
Ivan Kostrov?

549
00:44:43,130 --> 00:44:44,996
We're talking about him, right?

550
00:44:45,130 --> 00:44:47,029
Of course I do. You bet.

551
00:44:47,729 --> 00:44:49,162
We're pals.

552
00:44:49,262 --> 00:44:50,895
He's a lawyer, I'm a lawyer.

553
00:44:51,562 --> 00:44:53,594
Moscow is a huge,
but close-knit city.

554
00:44:54,594 --> 00:44:57,461
No one is out of reach.

555
00:44:57,561 --> 00:45:00,560
And if I don't read this, then what?

556
00:45:00,693 --> 00:45:02,192
Doesn't matter.

557
00:45:02,292 --> 00:45:04,825
Take my word for it:
the facts in there are damning.

558
00:45:04,925 --> 00:45:08,558
You know what I'm talking about.
They are, after all, your handiwork.

559
00:45:08,658 --> 00:45:10,191
Horrible stuff.

560
00:45:10,824 --> 00:45:13,590
How do you sleep at night?

561
00:45:14,823 --> 00:45:16,023
So,

562
00:45:17,323 --> 00:45:18,622
let's make a deal, or else...

563
00:45:18,722 --> 00:45:20,122
Or else what?

564
00:45:21,488 --> 00:45:24,155
Oh, it's hard to even imagine
what would happen.

565
00:45:24,288 --> 00:45:27,487
All within the provisions of the law,
of course.

566
00:45:27,587 --> 00:45:31,153
Firstly, your name would be all over
the newspapers and the Internet

567
00:45:31,253 --> 00:45:34,319
and on TV, all over the news.

568
00:45:43,117 --> 00:45:45,783
You youngsters
like playing with fire.

569
00:45:45,883 --> 00:45:49,249
Vadim,
you're not exactly an old man either.

570
00:45:49,416 --> 00:45:51,549
Or is it time to retire? No?

571
00:45:51,615 --> 00:45:52,981
Have you thought of that?

572
00:45:54,781 --> 00:45:58,580
Come back with the tea later, Yulia.

573
00:46:03,313 --> 00:46:06,412
Right. Let's see it.

574
00:46:08,112 --> 00:46:11,411
Let's see what you're trying
to stick us with here.

575
00:46:11,511 --> 00:46:14,610
A horror movie with you in the lead.

576
00:46:14,710 --> 00:46:19,109
How did it go? They cuffed him
and threw him in the cage.

577
00:46:19,843 --> 00:46:21,542
What did he do? Nothing!

578
00:46:21,642 --> 00:46:25,674
Last night, the mayor barreled in,
drunk, told 'em to pack their things.

579
00:46:25,808 --> 00:46:27,541
They had
another court hearing yesterday.

580
00:46:27,674 --> 00:46:29,207
Yes, they're getting demolished.

581
00:46:29,973 --> 00:46:31,307
That's all.

582
00:46:31,440 --> 00:46:35,406
This morning, they went to the police
to drop off a statement

583
00:46:35,506 --> 00:46:37,239
and they took Kolya in.

584
00:46:39,805 --> 00:46:41,938
Lilya is sitting right here with me.

585
00:46:42,604 --> 00:46:45,970
Don't be dumb,
I'm not calling just for a chat.

586
00:46:46,070 --> 00:46:49,436
Tell Stepanych to get his arse
to the police department.

587
00:46:49,569 --> 00:46:51,536
We have to get Kolya out of there.

588
00:46:53,002 --> 00:46:54,168
Good.

589
00:46:54,635 --> 00:46:56,335
Yeah, you'd better go yourself.

590
00:46:57,967 --> 00:47:00,900
And call us right away.
We're stressing out here.

591
00:47:01,000 --> 00:47:05,233
And pick up when I call,
or I'll worry. OK then.

592
00:47:05,333 --> 00:47:06,333
What?

593
00:47:06,999 --> 00:47:08,099
Me too.

594
00:47:09,365 --> 00:47:11,564
OK, Pasha, go already. Bye.

595
00:47:13,231 --> 00:47:15,231
- Something like that.
- Thanks.

596
00:47:15,331 --> 00:47:17,530
Don't worry, they'll get him out.

597
00:47:17,663 --> 00:47:21,330
They got Vova out 5 times.
He was in for real stuff - fighting,

598
00:47:21,462 --> 00:47:23,196
theft...

599
00:47:23,329 --> 00:47:25,162
Mum, I'm hungry.

600
00:47:25,295 --> 00:47:26,895
Go play outside.
Dinner's not ready yet.

601
00:47:26,995 --> 00:47:29,094
- Can I?
- What?

602
00:47:29,194 --> 00:47:31,160
- Go outside?
- I just told you, go!

603
00:47:31,294 --> 00:47:34,759
But not too far. If you go
to building 9 again, I'll kill you!

604
00:47:34,859 --> 00:47:36,459
- OK, Mum!
- And put your hat on!

605
00:47:44,691 --> 00:47:45,924
Come on in.

606
00:47:55,855 --> 00:47:58,088
It's OK, honey. We'll pull through.

607
00:47:58,688 --> 00:48:02,387
We'll get all hands on deck
and do a great job.

608
00:48:03,920 --> 00:48:07,720
Won't be fancy, but it'll be homely.

609
00:48:07,819 --> 00:48:08,852
Won't it?

610
00:48:13,951 --> 00:48:15,751
Let's go look at the kitchen.

611
00:48:20,583 --> 00:48:22,549
There's even a radiator in here.

612
00:48:23,449 --> 00:48:24,516
You hear me?

613
00:48:30,515 --> 00:48:32,447
Let's say you got me. Now what?

614
00:48:32,880 --> 00:48:34,114
That depends on you.

615
00:48:34,247 --> 00:48:36,713
I got that much. What do you want?

616
00:48:39,545 --> 00:48:43,745
You're the second public official today
to use that tone with me.

617
00:48:43,845 --> 00:48:46,977
Don't beat around the bush.
Get to the point.

618
00:48:48,444 --> 00:48:50,943
I want Kolya to keep what's his.

619
00:48:55,442 --> 00:48:57,042
That's not possible.

620
00:49:00,041 --> 00:49:02,241
I thought there was
nothing impossible for you.

621
00:49:03,307 --> 00:49:05,707
Well, now you know better.

622
00:49:05,807 --> 00:49:08,473
You can't get 3.5 million?
I don't believe that.

623
00:49:08,606 --> 00:49:10,639
Oh, that's what you mean.

624
00:49:11,806 --> 00:49:13,272
That I can do.

625
00:49:13,372 --> 00:49:15,471
And, of course, release Kolya.

626
00:49:15,605 --> 00:49:17,005
It's a deal.

627
00:49:18,337 --> 00:49:20,070
Leave me your phone number.

628
00:49:20,704 --> 00:49:23,936
I'll call you in a couple of days.
We'll meet and discuss the details.

629
00:49:24,603 --> 00:49:25,635
You'll still be here?

630
00:49:25,735 --> 00:49:26,969
Yes, I'll be in town.

631
00:49:27,435 --> 00:49:29,202
Except what's there to discuss?

632
00:49:30,202 --> 00:49:33,667
We'll only need to meet
so you can hand me the money.

633
00:49:36,867 --> 00:49:40,366
Hey, are you baptised?

634
00:49:40,499 --> 00:49:41,499
What?

635
00:49:42,632 --> 00:49:44,299
Why da you ask?

636
00:49:44,799 --> 00:49:46,431
I'm just curious.

637
00:49:48,031 --> 00:49:50,297
I'm a lawyer, Vadim.
I believe in facts.

638
00:49:56,829 --> 00:49:57,129
OK. You got it.

639
00:49:57,129 --> 00:49:58,296
Goodbye.

640
00:50:02,461 --> 00:50:03,661
Bye.

641
00:50:35,220 --> 00:50:38,087
Is everything OK, Vadim?

642
00:50:39,453 --> 00:50:39,686
Yes.

643
00:50:40,153 --> 00:50:42,319
You never brought me that aspirin.

644
00:50:44,452 --> 00:50:47,051
Get me those three right away.

645
00:50:48,317 --> 00:50:49,384
Who?

646
00:50:49,517 --> 00:50:52,116
Tarasov, Goryunov and Tkachuk.

647
00:50:52,816 --> 00:50:55,083
Find them, I don't care how.

648
00:50:58,715 --> 00:51:00,215
And close the door.

649
00:51:00,348 --> 00:51:02,314
You think
he'll give us the 3 million?

650
00:51:02,448 --> 00:51:04,514
Not 3, but 3.5.

651
00:51:04,647 --> 00:51:05,947
We'll see.

652
00:51:06,481 --> 00:51:09,413
But he shit himself big time.
And that's a good sign.

653
00:51:10,980 --> 00:51:12,312
Right...

654
00:51:13,279 --> 00:51:16,611
What did I have here last time?

655
00:51:16,745 --> 00:51:18,678
Borscht, dumplings, beer.

656
00:51:18,811 --> 00:51:20,210
That's it.

657
00:51:20,344 --> 00:51:21,510
Have you decided?

658
00:51:21,577 --> 00:51:24,677
Yes, Tatyana.
Bring us two borschts, please,

659
00:51:25,143 --> 00:51:28,509
two servings of dumplings,
beer and fruit juice.

660
00:51:28,642 --> 00:51:30,208
Or are you having beer too?

661
00:51:30,342 --> 00:51:31,842
Fruit juice is fine.

662
00:51:31,975 --> 00:51:33,175
- Fruit juice then.
- Is that it?

663
00:51:33,308 --> 00:51:34,375
Yes, that's all.

664
00:51:34,475 --> 00:51:37,107
I have to go up to my room.

665
00:51:37,207 --> 00:51:39,673
Please wait 10 minutes
so the food doesn't get cold.

666
00:51:40,606 --> 00:51:42,473
- All right.
- Thanks.

667
00:51:44,872 --> 00:51:47,105
Can you wait a bit?
I'll be right back.

668
00:52:59,756 --> 00:53:00,822
Kolya?

669
00:53:00,956 --> 00:53:02,288
<i>Hello, where are you?</i>

670
00:53:02,422 --> 00:53:05,455
We're in the restaurant at the hotel.

671
00:53:05,555 --> 00:53:06,621
Well, of course.

672
00:53:06,755 --> 00:53:10,954
I'm behind bars - you're at a restaurant.
I should have known.

673
00:53:12,286 --> 00:53:13,986
Yes, they released me.

674
00:53:16,585 --> 00:53:21,218
Not on the phone.
Let's meet, and you'll tell me everything.

675
00:53:21,318 --> 00:53:23,017
Finish up.

676
00:53:23,151 --> 00:53:26,150
I'm headed there. See you.

677
00:53:59,443 --> 00:54:01,443
They've been keeping dirt on me!

678
00:54:01,576 --> 00:54:03,775
I've known it a long time.

679
00:54:03,909 --> 00:54:07,574
All I ever hear from you is
the same thing right, left and centre:

680
00:54:07,674 --> 00:54:11,441
"Everything's fine, Vadim".

681
00:54:12,240 --> 00:54:14,473
"Everything's fine, perfect weather -

682
00:54:14,973 --> 00:54:16,872
"nothing to worry about!"

683
00:54:17,006 --> 00:54:19,572
But I'm fucking worried!

684
00:54:20,771 --> 00:54:24,838
Because I smell a rat.
Something bad is brewing!

685
00:54:25,004 --> 00:54:28,170
When did anything like this
ever happen? I crush some louse

686
00:54:28,303 --> 00:54:33,169
and he turns the tables on me!
Brings in a lawyer from Moscow!

687
00:54:33,302 --> 00:54:35,935
And that bastard starts
blackmailing me.

688
00:54:36,068 --> 00:54:38,068
And drops big names!

689
00:54:38,168 --> 00:54:39,934
What if he's bluffing?

690
00:54:40,034 --> 00:54:41,201
Bluffing?

691
00:54:41,301 --> 00:54:45,300
How about you stop doodling
and figure out who's paying him?

692
00:54:45,433 --> 00:54:47,033
You think it's that loser Kolya?

693
00:54:47,133 --> 00:54:49,365
You should know better, woman.

694
00:54:49,465 --> 00:54:54,364
Or do you think
that Moscow lawyer came here

695
00:54:54,498 --> 00:54:56,197
to bust his arse for free?

696
00:54:56,297 --> 00:54:57,597
More importantly,

697
00:54:57,731 --> 00:55:00,963
where did he get that information?

698
00:55:02,430 --> 00:55:05,762
I almost fucking lost it
when I opened that folder.

699
00:55:05,862 --> 00:55:08,395
So what was in that folder?

700
00:55:08,495 --> 00:55:11,428
You don't need to know that.

701
00:55:14,493 --> 00:55:18,826
So they have something on you
that we don't know about?

702
00:55:18,926 --> 00:55:21,258
We have an election in a year.

703
00:55:21,392 --> 00:55:22,592
Did you forget?

704
00:55:23,958 --> 00:55:25,991
If I don't get elected...

705
00:55:27,024 --> 00:55:28,457
Need I say more?

706
00:55:31,323 --> 00:55:33,556
You'll all go down.

707
00:55:34,189 --> 00:55:36,489
No holidays abroad, no mansions,

708
00:55:37,222 --> 00:55:38,255
no cash.

709
00:55:39,222 --> 00:55:41,588
We'll all be marching

710
00:55:41,688 --> 00:55:43,753
off to the monastery

711
00:55:43,853 --> 00:55:45,853
to a jolly tune.

712
00:55:45,953 --> 00:55:47,820
You're paranoid.

713
00:55:47,953 --> 00:55:50,886
You see enemies everywhere.
Ease up on the booze.

714
00:55:51,719 --> 00:55:55,118
Your head will roll first!

715
00:55:55,251 --> 00:55:58,750
Cut the drama.
And don't yell at me!

716
00:55:58,850 --> 00:56:00,883
Save that for your wife.

717
00:56:01,450 --> 00:56:03,516
Let's be constructive.

718
00:56:03,616 --> 00:56:04,882
Let's.

719
00:56:06,416 --> 00:56:08,915
Maybe I could lean on him a bit?

720
00:56:09,548 --> 00:56:12,247
Within lawful limits, of course.

721
00:56:12,381 --> 00:56:13,947
Absolutely not.

722
00:56:16,414 --> 00:56:20,745
First off, get me the story
on this Moscow lawyer.

723
00:56:22,079 --> 00:56:27,678
Use your own channels or work together,
but find out who he is

724
00:56:28,377 --> 00:56:30,877
and who he's working for.

725
00:56:31,643 --> 00:56:34,742
He was rubbing it in
about Kostrov,

726
00:56:34,876 --> 00:56:36,609
and you say "lean on him"?

727
00:56:36,742 --> 00:56:38,409
The Committee Chairman?

728
00:56:39,075 --> 00:56:43,808
That's right, sweetheart. Why do you
think I've been going on about it?

729
00:56:47,307 --> 00:56:48,739
So get to it.

730
00:56:49,739 --> 00:56:51,439
Tomorrow, I'll consult the bosses.

731
00:56:51,506 --> 00:56:56,238
They're going
to run their checks on him.

732
00:56:57,271 --> 00:57:00,470
Get to it, my good people,
and get cracking.

733
00:57:22,366 --> 00:57:23,366
Hello, Dad...

734
00:57:23,832 --> 00:57:25,332
But it's still early.

735
00:57:26,165 --> 00:57:29,898
Oh, I forgot...
Yeah, I'll be right there... Sure, OK.

736
00:57:30,564 --> 00:57:32,264
Yeah, I'm not far.

737
00:57:33,263 --> 00:57:35,163
OK, guys, I'm off.

738
00:57:36,263 --> 00:57:39,828
- Mummy calling you?
- We're going out shooting tomorrow.

739
00:57:39,962 --> 00:57:41,562
You're lucky!

740
00:57:42,428 --> 00:57:45,461
That's right,
go and watch your bedtime cartoons.

741
00:58:15,288 --> 00:58:16,820
Where is everyone?

742
00:58:17,354 --> 00:58:19,153
Mum is asleep.

743
00:58:19,253 --> 00:58:22,553
Dima's in the outhouse
with a magazine.

744
00:58:28,185 --> 00:58:29,451
So, mate,

745
00:58:31,417 --> 00:58:33,217
you like Dima?

746
00:58:33,650 --> 00:58:35,783
Sure. Seems like an all right guy.

747
00:58:38,583 --> 00:58:41,682
That "all right guy"
did a major deed today.

748
00:58:42,448 --> 00:58:43,582
What deed?

749
00:58:44,214 --> 00:58:45,648
He squeezed the mayor.

750
00:58:47,181 --> 00:58:48,247
What?

751
00:58:48,913 --> 00:58:50,780
Just like that, son.

752
00:58:50,880 --> 00:58:52,613
Took him by the balls

753
00:58:53,346 --> 00:58:55,946
and pulled ever so gently.

754
00:58:58,978 --> 00:59:00,345
I don't get it.

755
00:59:01,411 --> 00:59:03,444
You'll get it when you're older.

756
00:59:03,544 --> 00:59:04,710
Listen,

757
00:59:05,177 --> 00:59:07,110
you stink of fire.

758
00:59:07,243 --> 00:59:09,376
Hanging out
in the old church again?

759
00:59:09,509 --> 00:59:10,509
Well, yeah.

760
00:59:11,109 --> 00:59:12,775
Always looking for trouble.

761
00:59:14,042 --> 00:59:17,307
- What kind of trouble?
- Some kind or other.

762
00:59:18,541 --> 00:59:21,274
Stuffing your face right before bed?

763
00:59:22,706 --> 00:59:23,706
Well, yeah.

764
00:59:30,005 --> 00:59:31,371
Come over here.

765
00:59:32,104 --> 00:59:33,137
Sit down.

766
00:59:34,903 --> 00:59:36,203
What is it?

767
00:59:39,136 --> 00:59:40,536
Were you drinking beer?

768
00:59:42,202 --> 00:59:44,635
No. The other guys had some.

769
00:59:44,735 --> 00:59:46,501
I can smell it on you.

770
00:59:46,601 --> 00:59:47,701
Hey, Roma.

771
00:59:51,100 --> 00:59:52,400
What took you so long?

772
00:59:52,533 --> 00:59:54,333
Lay a cable out there?

773
00:59:54,999 --> 00:59:57,399
Interesting book
you've got out there.

774
00:59:58,898 --> 01:00:00,831
Couldn't put it down?

775
01:00:02,831 --> 01:00:03,897
Yeah...

776
01:00:07,396 --> 01:00:08,996
A couple of comedians, eh?

777
01:00:10,096 --> 01:00:14,662
Yeah, that's our shitty
northern sense of humour.

778
01:00:20,627 --> 01:00:22,260
What's so funny?

779
01:00:22,393 --> 01:00:25,626
It's all good, bro.

780
01:00:26,959 --> 01:00:28,692
It's all good.

781
01:00:29,225 --> 01:00:30,991
No, seriously, what am I missing?

782
01:00:33,025 --> 01:00:34,658
Whatever, you idiots...

783
01:03:03,458 --> 01:03:05,725
Can you do this?

784
01:03:05,825 --> 01:03:08,091
I'll show you. Watch.

785
01:03:11,024 --> 01:03:13,090
Pasha, turn off that crap.

786
01:03:15,489 --> 01:03:16,856
Dima!

787
01:03:17,355 --> 01:03:18,889
Come here for a moment.

788
01:03:22,621 --> 01:03:24,221
Pasha, what the hell?

789
01:03:24,321 --> 01:03:27,087
Angela, let's enjoy the silence.

790
01:03:27,187 --> 01:03:29,320
Not enough silence at your place?

791
01:03:31,052 --> 01:03:32,119
Dima,

792
01:03:32,719 --> 01:03:35,419
- I'm trusting you with my rifle.
- Thanks.

793
01:03:35,585 --> 01:03:38,085
Every guy should have his own gun,

794
01:03:38,185 --> 01:03:40,118
so you don't have to share Kolya's.

795
01:03:40,250 --> 01:03:41,484
Agreed.

796
01:03:42,350 --> 01:03:44,017
What will you use then?

797
01:03:44,150 --> 01:03:45,683
I'll show you.

798
01:03:45,816 --> 01:03:46,983
You need help, Kolya?

799
01:03:47,116 --> 01:03:50,182
No, Dima, I've got this.
Relax, kick back.

800
01:03:50,315 --> 01:03:51,482
You're the guest.

801
01:03:53,748 --> 01:03:55,347
Wow, Stepanych!

802
01:03:55,481 --> 01:03:56,914
Someone's armed for war.

803
01:03:57,047 --> 01:04:00,046
Why not? I like shooting in style.
It's my birthday.

804
01:04:00,180 --> 01:04:04,179
- What, no grenade launcher?
- Show me the target, I'll get one.

805
01:04:06,978 --> 01:04:09,978
- Mum, I'm thirsty.
- It's in the car.

806
01:04:13,277 --> 01:04:16,043
Where are you going?
Out of the water, now!

807
01:04:16,110 --> 01:04:19,209
Vitya, are you deaf?
I said, get out of the water!

808
01:04:22,609 --> 01:04:23,841
So, Kolya,

809
01:04:25,041 --> 01:04:26,308
shall we?

810
01:04:30,340 --> 01:04:31,607
Sure.

811
01:04:32,339 --> 01:04:33,339
Dima,

812
01:04:33,939 --> 01:04:35,206
Pasha, come on!

813
01:05:16,997 --> 01:05:18,229
Dima,

814
01:05:19,163 --> 01:05:22,362
one drink if you hit it,
three if you miss.

815
01:05:22,496 --> 01:05:23,962
Got it.

816
01:05:29,360 --> 01:05:30,727
One drink!

817
01:05:34,126 --> 01:05:35,393
Just one!

818
01:05:35,493 --> 01:05:37,892
To your health, Stepanych!
Cheers!

819
01:05:37,992 --> 01:05:39,325
Same to you.

820
01:05:40,692 --> 01:05:43,058
Go, Pasha. Nail it.

821
01:05:43,158 --> 01:05:44,791
Don't jinx me.

822
01:05:53,322 --> 01:05:54,355
Three drinks for him.

823
01:05:54,455 --> 01:05:57,154
He missed on purpose,
to get shitfaced.

824
01:05:57,854 --> 01:05:59,688
- Just pour it.
- Have a pickle.

825
01:05:59,820 --> 01:06:01,320
To you, Comrade Colonel.

826
01:06:02,620 --> 01:06:04,619
Dima, you show them.

827
01:06:09,818 --> 01:06:11,951
Anyone can hit it with a sight.

828
01:06:13,051 --> 01:06:14,451
The sight was closed.

829
01:06:14,551 --> 01:06:16,350
Are you for me or against me?

830
01:06:17,850 --> 01:06:19,150
Stepanych.

831
01:06:19,216 --> 01:06:21,949
Pleasure to meet you,
happy birthday!

832
01:06:22,049 --> 01:06:23,315
Pleasure's all mine.

833
01:06:28,781 --> 01:06:29,914
Stepanych, just don't...

834
01:06:33,913 --> 01:06:35,313
Enjoying the silence?

835
01:06:35,446 --> 01:06:37,079
What did you do that for?

836
01:06:37,179 --> 01:06:39,412
What do we use for a target now?

837
01:06:39,512 --> 01:06:42,345
Your hat? Are you fucking crazy?

838
01:06:42,445 --> 01:06:43,744
Kolya,  the kids...

839
01:06:43,844 --> 01:06:46,810
What about the kids?
They just went deaf.

840
01:06:46,944 --> 01:06:48,143
No, I heard everything.

841
01:06:48,277 --> 01:06:51,743
Can't I shoot to my heart's content
on my birthday?

842
01:06:51,843 --> 01:06:52,876
Well, now you have.

843
01:06:53,042 --> 01:06:56,042
I've got better targets still.

844
01:06:57,775 --> 01:06:59,041
Pasha!

845
01:06:59,175 --> 01:07:00,307
Go get them.

846
01:07:00,441 --> 01:07:02,940
Angela, shall we get started
on the kebabs?

847
01:07:05,106 --> 01:07:08,039
- Can I shoot the AK, please?
- Ask Stepanych.

848
01:07:08,139 --> 01:07:10,739
Stepanych, can I fire your AK?

849
01:07:10,839 --> 01:07:12,105
Sure.

850
01:07:12,572 --> 01:07:15,171
He's a grown boy. Let him.

851
01:07:15,304 --> 01:07:17,603
Stay with us, gals.
It's about to get interesting.

852
01:07:17,703 --> 01:07:19,837
Call us when it does.

853
01:07:21,436 --> 01:07:24,269
- I'll go and light the grill.
- Can you manage?

854
01:07:25,102 --> 01:07:26,135
I think so...

855
01:07:34,500 --> 01:07:36,767
Nice one, Stepanych!

856
01:07:39,132 --> 01:07:41,232
Got anyone more current?

857
01:07:41,332 --> 01:07:43,998
I've got all kinds of stuff.

858
01:07:44,131 --> 01:07:46,797
But it's too early
for the current ones.

859
01:07:46,864 --> 01:07:49,230
Not enough
of a historical perspective.

860
01:07:49,364 --> 01:07:51,730
Let them ripen up on the wall a bit.

861
01:07:52,929 --> 01:07:53,963
How do we stand them up?

862
01:07:54,096 --> 01:07:56,395
Nail them to the log.

863
01:07:57,062 --> 01:07:58,328
Do we have nails?

864
01:07:58,862 --> 01:07:59,928
No.

865
01:08:00,494 --> 01:08:02,294
I've got some screws in the car.

866
01:08:09,226 --> 01:08:10,759
Let's go have a drink.

867
01:08:10,892 --> 01:08:12,125
Let's.

868
01:08:17,958 --> 01:08:19,924
I've got Yeltsin, too.

869
01:08:21,723 --> 01:08:24,389
But he's more small-time.

870
01:08:25,489 --> 01:08:26,956
The drunken conductor...

871
01:08:28,288 --> 01:08:30,621
We forgot the nails...
Your fault.

872
01:08:30,755 --> 01:08:33,554
Look at you, girls!
There's a sight for sore eyes!

873
01:08:33,687 --> 01:08:36,087
Look at those honed,
precise movements!

874
01:08:36,220 --> 01:08:37,586
Yeah.

875
01:08:37,720 --> 01:08:39,486
We're quite the roadside attraction!

876
01:08:48,284 --> 01:08:50,751
- Any bread?
- In the bag.

877
01:08:50,851 --> 01:08:54,350
- What else is there?
- Pickles.

878
01:08:54,450 --> 01:08:56,216
- Help me.
- I'm busy.

879
01:08:56,316 --> 01:08:59,115
- I'm busy too.
- What are you busy with?

880
01:08:59,249 --> 01:09:00,448
With stuff...

881
01:09:03,014 --> 01:09:06,580
Kolya, come here! Let's drink.

882
01:09:16,078 --> 01:09:17,378
That's enough.

883
01:09:17,811 --> 01:09:21,177
My oh my, what a guy...

884
01:09:23,943 --> 01:09:25,509
Where are you off to, Lilya?

885
01:09:26,076 --> 01:09:28,075
Wouldn't you like to know?

886
01:09:28,209 --> 01:09:30,275
Did we bring the charcoal?

887
01:09:30,408 --> 01:09:32,708
- What for?
- We'll run out of wood.

888
01:09:32,808 --> 01:09:36,407
Plenty of driftwood.
Go get some, but have a drink first.

889
01:09:36,541 --> 01:09:38,040
Chase it down.

890
01:09:39,540 --> 01:09:42,039
Where's my drink?

891
01:09:42,139 --> 01:09:43,306
Here you are.

892
01:09:44,705 --> 01:09:46,071
Thank you.

893
01:09:49,371 --> 01:09:51,470
Oh, this is nice!

894
01:09:53,203 --> 01:09:56,603
- Where is that wood, you say?
- Past the waterfall. You'll see it.

895
01:09:56,736 --> 01:09:57,902
Got it.

896
01:10:10,266 --> 01:10:12,633
Vitya, come down here.

897
01:10:12,733 --> 01:10:13,799
I'm scared.

898
01:10:13,933 --> 01:10:15,532
- Give me your hand.
- No, I'm scared.

899
01:10:17,265 --> 01:10:19,098
Suit yourself.

900
01:10:28,629 --> 01:10:30,129
Where's your kid?

901
01:10:30,229 --> 01:10:31,762
And where's yours?

902
01:10:36,494 --> 01:10:38,160
He'll break his neck.

903
01:10:38,260 --> 01:10:40,127
He'll be fine.

904
01:10:40,260 --> 01:10:44,126
Let him run around and enjoy nature.
There are no animals here.

905
01:10:44,292 --> 01:10:46,858
Man is the most dangerous animal.

906
01:10:46,958 --> 01:10:49,591
- None of those here either.
- Well, we're here.

907
01:10:49,725 --> 01:10:53,190
- You calling yourself a man?
- Get a handle on your woman, Pasha.

908
01:10:53,290 --> 01:10:55,024
Too late now.

909
01:10:57,456 --> 01:10:58,789
Mummy!

910
01:11:00,822 --> 01:11:02,355
What happened, Vitya?

911
01:11:02,455 --> 01:11:05,188
That man is choking Lilya.

912
01:11:05,288 --> 01:11:06,921
Roma saw it and started crying.

913
01:11:07,054 --> 01:11:09,153
What are you talking about? What man?

914
01:11:09,253 --> 01:11:11,153
The handsome one from Moscow.

915
01:11:18,085 --> 01:11:19,318
You coppers

916
01:11:19,418 --> 01:11:21,784
just gonna wait
for the mayhem to start?

917
01:11:22,351 --> 01:11:24,517
Mum, what's "mayhem"?

918
01:11:26,450 --> 01:11:29,049
- You'll know when you're older.
- I want to know now.

919
01:11:29,183 --> 01:11:31,682
Let's put that gun away

920
01:11:32,416 --> 01:11:33,782
from harm.

921
01:11:39,014 --> 01:11:40,647
Mum, what's "harm"?

922
01:11:40,747 --> 01:11:44,313
Stop annoying me.
Remember when you set the cat on fire?

923
01:11:44,913 --> 01:11:48,412
- Yeah. Who did it this time?
- Nobody.

924
01:11:48,545 --> 01:11:51,544
- Then where's the harm?
- Knock it off.

925
01:11:53,211 --> 01:11:54,577
Oh, God...

926
01:11:55,311 --> 01:11:57,577
You've got too anxious, Vadim.

927
01:11:57,710 --> 01:12:01,976
Worrying yourself and others
over nothing.

928
01:12:02,076 --> 01:12:04,142
As if you don't know

929
01:12:04,242 --> 01:12:07,574
we're all in God's hands.
It's His will.

930
01:12:07,708 --> 01:12:10,674
Of course I know, Father.

931
01:12:10,807 --> 01:12:12,440
So what troubles you?

932
01:12:12,940 --> 01:12:15,173
Is your faith wavering?

933
01:12:16,039 --> 01:12:18,538
Do you take communion?
Go to confession?

934
01:12:20,138 --> 01:12:22,171
Every Sunday, without fail.

935
01:12:23,137 --> 01:12:24,404
I try to.

936
01:12:25,104 --> 01:12:28,436
Of course I can't always make it.
I get so busy...

937
01:12:28,536 --> 01:12:30,070
But I try.

938
01:12:31,203 --> 01:12:33,302
Who's your confessor?

939
01:12:37,002 --> 01:12:41,001
Our local priest,
the one you referred me to.

940
01:12:41,101 --> 01:12:42,567
Father Alexei?

941
01:12:42,700 --> 01:12:44,067
That's the one.

942
01:12:45,200 --> 01:12:47,166
He's a good priest.

943
01:12:47,732 --> 01:12:49,432
Seems OK.

944
01:12:50,899 --> 01:12:52,965
Get a hold of yourself, Vadim.

945
01:12:53,065 --> 01:12:56,198
And don't worry,
you are doing God's work.

946
01:12:56,864 --> 01:12:59,497
It is said
that good deeds are done

947
01:12:59,597 --> 01:13:01,829
happily and with ease,

948
01:13:02,796 --> 01:13:04,529
but don't forget

949
01:13:04,628 --> 01:13:07,761
the enemy is ever ready
and does not sleep.

950
01:13:07,861 --> 01:13:09,627
That's the thing.

951
01:13:09,727 --> 01:13:11,794
You know...

952
01:13:12,327 --> 01:13:14,694
It's like everything is going wrong.

953
01:13:15,926 --> 01:13:16,659
I'm uneasy.

954
01:13:17,193 --> 01:13:18,159
I'm uneasy.

955
01:13:18,893 --> 01:13:19,992
What's happened is...

956
01:13:20,092 --> 01:13:23,492
Don't reveal anything to me.
You're not at confession.

957
01:13:25,324 --> 01:13:27,491
You and I may be working

958
01:13:28,023 --> 01:13:29,657
for the same cause.

959
01:13:30,223 --> 01:13:34,222
But you've got your territory,
and I've got mine.

960
01:13:34,356 --> 01:13:36,322
I understand that.

961
01:13:39,088 --> 01:13:41,154
I just feel ill at ease...

962
01:13:42,154 --> 01:13:46,020
I told you a couple of days ago,
and I'll tell you again:

963
01:13:46,153 --> 01:13:48,319
all power is from God.

964
01:13:48,886 --> 01:13:51,252
Where there's power, there's might.

965
01:13:51,386 --> 01:13:55,351
If you hold power in your territory,

966
01:13:56,017 --> 01:14:00,184
solve your issues yourself,
with your might.

967
01:14:00,316 --> 01:14:03,116
Don't go looking for help,

968
01:14:03,216 --> 01:14:05,815
or the enemy will think
you are weak.

969
01:14:08,715 --> 01:14:11,748
Honestly, I have to lecture you
like a child.

970
01:14:11,881 --> 01:14:12,881
Vadim...

971
01:14:14,313 --> 01:14:16,180
I don't recognise you like this.

972
01:14:18,680 --> 01:14:20,479
Everything OK with the wife?

973
01:14:21,346 --> 01:14:22,912
I think so.

974
01:14:23,045 --> 01:14:24,445
How are the kids?

975
01:14:25,178 --> 01:14:26,744
They're fine.

976
01:14:28,010 --> 01:14:29,477
You're not sick?

977
01:14:32,177 --> 01:14:33,609
No.

978
01:14:39,642 --> 01:14:41,608
That's a blessing.

979
01:14:50,606 --> 01:14:52,372
God bless you.

980
01:15:51,093 --> 01:15:53,326
It's all my fault.

981
01:15:53,459 --> 01:15:55,359
No such thing.

982
01:15:56,359 --> 01:15:58,858
Each of us is guilty
of our own faults.

983
01:16:00,124 --> 01:16:02,324
Everything is everyone's fault.

984
01:16:04,157 --> 01:16:06,656
Even if we confess,

985
01:16:07,089 --> 01:16:10,056
the law doesn't hold it
to be a proof of guilt.

986
01:16:12,022 --> 01:16:15,021
We're innocent until proven guilty.

987
01:16:19,186 --> 01:16:22,353
But who's going to prove anything?
And to whom?

988
01:16:26,352 --> 01:16:28,118
Do you believe in God?

989
01:16:29,784 --> 01:16:32,251
Why do you all keep
asking me about God?

990
01:16:32,351 --> 01:16:33,883
I believe in facts.

991
01:16:34,017 --> 01:16:35,850
I'm a lawyer, Lilya.

992
01:16:44,948 --> 01:16:47,947
Don't. Please.

993
01:16:48,880 --> 01:16:50,647
No confessions.

994
01:16:56,478 --> 01:16:59,011
Because there's no proof?

995
01:17:01,444 --> 01:17:03,077
And there won't be any.

996
01:17:10,643 --> 01:17:12,775
Will you come with me?

997
01:17:20,707 --> 01:17:23,106
I don't understand you.

998
01:17:24,839 --> 01:17:27,005
I don't understand myself.

999
01:18:09,030 --> 01:18:12,262
I'd love to run away
with someone too.

1000
01:18:13,562 --> 01:18:15,061
Women are dumb.

1001
01:18:16,761 --> 01:18:18,161
Why?

1002
01:18:20,127 --> 01:18:22,427
Because you can't run away
from yourself.

1003
01:18:23,660 --> 01:18:24,926
Maybe not,

1004
01:18:25,059 --> 01:18:27,826
but I sure can run away from you.

1005
01:18:30,792 --> 01:18:32,358
Where to?

1006
01:18:33,725 --> 01:18:35,457
To whore around in Moscow?

1007
01:18:35,557 --> 01:18:37,590
- Why "whore around"?
- Because you're a whore.

1008
01:18:41,623 --> 01:18:42,955
See that?

1009
01:18:43,055 --> 01:18:44,255
Want me to smack you too?

1010
01:18:44,389 --> 01:18:45,455
What?

1011
01:18:46,222 --> 01:18:49,121
You guys can't take a joke?

1012
01:18:50,987 --> 01:18:55,153
I think I'd run
all the way to America.

1013
01:18:56,086 --> 01:18:58,819
Great. Why not the moon?

1014
01:18:58,952 --> 01:19:01,551
Are you asking for another slap?

1015
01:19:03,651 --> 01:19:05,418
Are the boys asleep?

1016
01:19:06,018 --> 01:19:07,417
Yeah.

1017
01:19:09,217 --> 01:19:10,949
Roma...

1018
01:19:12,383 --> 01:19:13,549
he's...

1019
01:19:14,716 --> 01:19:15,982
depressed.

1020
01:19:16,515 --> 01:19:18,215
That's understandable.

1021
01:19:19,647 --> 01:19:21,614
I'll talk to him tomorrow.

1022
01:19:22,680 --> 01:19:23,880
Kolya,

1023
01:19:25,080 --> 01:19:26,380
don't drink so much again.

1024
01:19:28,279 --> 01:19:31,578
Roma's traumatised enough as it is.

1025
01:19:32,078 --> 01:19:33,544
I won't.

1026
01:19:35,911 --> 01:19:36,944
Good.

1027
01:19:57,673 --> 01:19:59,306
She's back.

1028
01:20:00,972 --> 01:20:03,838
- Thank God.
- Maybe she's getting her things.

1029
01:20:04,605 --> 01:20:08,737
Shut up, Pasha. Go get Vitya.

1030
01:20:10,904 --> 01:20:12,670
Are you OK to drive?

1031
01:20:14,169 --> 01:20:15,902
I'm a traffic cop, aren't I?

1032
01:20:36,431 --> 01:20:37,764
Vitya...

1033
01:20:46,629 --> 01:20:49,495
Well, we'll be off.

1034
01:20:50,628 --> 01:20:52,461
So just, you know...

1035
01:21:24,354 --> 01:21:25,554
Kolya...

1036
01:21:37,951 --> 01:21:39,951
Do you want a child?

1037
01:22:12,877 --> 01:22:15,043
Hello? Yes, Vadim.

1038
01:22:16,176 --> 01:22:17,843
Yes, I recognised you.

1039
01:22:21,908 --> 01:22:23,841
Sure, let's meet.

1040
01:22:25,841 --> 01:22:27,340
I'm at the hotel.

1041
01:22:30,873 --> 01:22:32,639
Half an hour is good.

1042
01:22:46,370 --> 01:22:48,070
Can I see those?

1043
01:22:48,202 --> 01:22:49,402
These?

1044
01:22:54,335 --> 01:22:55,834
- Here you are.
- Thanks.

1045
01:23:22,262 --> 01:23:24,162
Well, get in.

1046
01:23:24,962 --> 01:23:27,394
I won't bite. Come on!

1047
01:23:28,194 --> 01:23:29,293
You're a tough guy.

1048
01:23:29,393 --> 01:23:30,860
If I'm not back here in two hours...

1049
01:23:30,960 --> 01:23:33,093
You will be, don't worry.

1050
01:23:44,424 --> 01:23:46,223
